review_blob:
500 ml bottled. 

aroma: caramel (inappropriate according to bjcp), malt.
appearance: deep copper - amber colour, long lasting very thin white head, very clear. 
flavor: caramel malt is dominating, malty, complex, slightly bitter at the end.
mouthfeel: full bodied, chewy, smooth, moderate carbonation. 

not a typical vienna lager, but a very nice, complex, drinkable beer.

500 ml bottled.

aroma: herb, malt.
appearance: light copper colour, long lasting thin white head, very clear.
flavor: slightly sweet, malty, moderate bitter at the end, moderate herb.
mouthfeel: medium-light body, smooth, medium carbonation.

it is a clean refreshing (vienna type?) lager beer, very drinkable, ideal for summer (except the higher alcohol content).

Very pale colour, hazy. Thin, long lasting white head. Peppery nose, grainy (unmalted) taste, no hop aroma Medium bodied smooth, silky mouthfeel, a bit over carbonated with medium bitter finish.

Very refreshing, drinkable beer.

Bought in Tesco (Zywiec).
